{"id": 239721100, "title": "Harry Redknapp swaps football for racing as punter now owns '20-something' horses", "text": "Harry Redknap has swapped his title of king of the jungle for king of the paddock \u2013 owning 20 horses. The racing-mad footie legend and 2018 I\u2019m a Celebrity winner built up his stable while pretending to wife Sandra that he had just one nag. Harry, 77, said: \u201cMy wife used to think I only had the one horse. Now she says I have too many as I\u2019ve bought a few since retiring. \u201cI\u2019ve got 20-something now and they\u2019re all good horses.\u201d The former Spurs, West Ham, Bournemouth, Southampton and Portsmouth manager bought his first, Slick Cherry, in the late 1980s and enjoyed a 9-1 winner at Chepstow. Another, Shakem Up\u2019arry, won at Cheltenham at 8/1 in March. He added: \u201cWhen Shakem Up\u2019arry won at Cheltenham it was incredible \u2013 to have a winner there was just amazing.\u201d His other nags include Wake Up Harry, Moktasaab, Les Blues, Fascinating Lips, The Jukebox Man, Bowtogreatness, Moviesta, and Recoup. Other stars who have horses or are part-owners include Dame Judi Dench, Liz Hurley, Carol Vorderman, Richard Hammond, Ronnie Wood, Michael Owen and Mike Tindall. Harry has told how he and ex-Manchester United boss Sir Alex Ferguson \u2013 who reportedly owns 32 \u2013 used to bet on horses just before kick-off. He said: \u201cI would go to Old Trafford and I\u2019d take the team into the dressing room and Alex said, \u2018Come and have a cup of tea\u2019. \u201cI\u2019m in Fergie\u2019s office and me and Fergie are having a bet, we\u2019ve got the racing on, he\u2019s got the Racing Post. \u201cAt quarter to three he says, \u2018I\u2019ve got one in the 2.45\u2019, then suddenly I hear the players coming in \u2013 I hear their studs \u2013 and went, \u2018Alex, I\u2019d better go\u2019 but Alex said, \u2018No, no, they\u2019ve only two fences to go\u2019.\u201d Harry has teamed up with sports company Sorare to challenge punters to beat him in an online footie tournament during the Euros. Armchair fans take on other managers by creating a team and choosing tactics in a new free-to-play game called Sorare Rivals.", "summary": "Harry has always enjoyed a flutter and said himself and ex-Manchester United boss Sir Alex Ferguson used to bet on horses just before kick-of", "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/features/topic-desking/sport/harry-redknapp-swaps-football-racing-33087222", "image": "https://i2-prod.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article33087188.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Cheltenham-Festival-Horse-Racing-Races.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-23 00:07:02", "author": "Stian Alexander", "authors": ["Stian Alexander"], "language": "en", "catgory": "sports", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.256}